</ul>
<p><a name="Secondary_Sources" id="Secondary_Sources"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Critique_of_Pure_Reason&amp;action=edit&amp;section=32" title="Edit section: Secondary Sources">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Secondary Sources</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Martin Heidegger, <i>Kant and the Problem of Metaphysics 5th ed.</i> trans. Richard Taft. Indiana University Press: Bloomington (1973).</li>
<li>Arthur Schopenhauer, <i>The World as Will and Representation, Volume I, Appendix "Criticism of the Kantian Philosophy"</i>, Dover, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0486217612" class="internal">ISBN 0-486-21761-2</a></li>
<li>Bennett, J., KANT'S ANALYTIC (1966)</li>
<li>Bennett, J., KANT'S DIALECTIC (1974)</li>
<li>Cassirer, H., KANT'S FIRST CRITIQUE (1954)</li>
<li>Ewing, A. C., A SHORT COMMENTARY ON KANT'S CRITIQUE OF PURE REASON (1938)</li>
<li>Grayeff, F., KANT'S THEORETICAL PHILOSOPHY: A COMMENTARY TO THE CENTRAL PART OF THE CRITIQUE OF PURE REASON (1970)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.archive.org/details/commentarytokant00smituoft" class="external text" title="http://www.archive.org/details/commentarytokant00smituoft" rel="nofollow">Kemp Smith, N., A COMMENTARY ON KANT'S CRITIQUE OF PURE REASON (1918)</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Stephen_Palmquist" title="Stephen Palmquist">Palmquist, Stephen</a>, <a href="http://www.hkbu.edu.hk/~ppp/ksp1" class="external text" title="http://www.hkbu.edu.hk/~ppp/ksp1" rel="nofollow">Kant's System of Perspectives</a> (1993)</li>
<li>Paton, H. J., THE METAPHYSICS OF EXPERIENCE, 2 vols. (1936)</li>
<li>Pippin, R. B., KANT'S THEORY OF FORM: AN ESSAY ON THE CRITIQUE OF PURE REASON (1982)</li>
<li>Strawson, P. F., THE BOUNDS OF SENSE (1966)</li>
<li>Weldon, T. D., INTRODUCTION TO KANT'S CRITIQUE OF PURE REASON (1945)</li>
<li>Wilkerson, T. E., KANT'S CRITIQUE OF PURE REASON: A COMMENTARY FOR STUDENTS (1976)</li>
<li>Wolff, R. P., KANT'S THEORY OF MENTAL ACTIVITY (1962).</li>
<li>Allison, H. E., KANT'S TRANSCENDENTAL IDEALISM (1983)</li>
<li>Ameriks, K., KANT'S THEORY OF MIND (1982)</li>
<li>Aquila, R. E., MATTER IN MIND: A STUDY OF KANT'S TRANSCENDENTAL DEDUCTION (1989)</li>
<li>Aquila, R. E., REPRESENTATIONAL MIND: A STUDY OF KANT'S THEORY OF KNOWLEDGE (1983)</li>
<li>Azm, S. J., THE ORIGINS OF KANT'S ARGUMENTS IN THE ANTINOMIES (1972)</li>
<li>Beck, L. W., ESSAYS ON KANT AND HUME (1978)</li>
<li>Beck, L. W., STUDIES IN THE PHILOSOPHY OF KANT (1969)</li>
<li>Bencivenza, E., KANT'S COPERNICAN REVOLUTION (1987)</li>
<li>Bird, G., KANT'S THEORY OF KNOWLEDGE (1962)</li>
<li>Broad, C. D., KANT: AN INTRODUCTION (1978)</li>
<li>Buchdahl, G., KANT AND THE DYNAMICS OF REASON (1992)</li>
<li>Butts, R. E., KANT AND THE DOUBLE GOVERNMENT METHODOLOG6Y:. . .KANT'S PHILOSOPHY OF SCIENCE (1984)</li>
<li>Carnois, B., THE COHERENCE OF KANT'S DOCTRINE OF FREEDOM (1987)</li>
<li>Deleuze, G., KANT'S CRITICAL PHILOSOPHY: THE DOCTRINE OF THE FACULTIES (1984)</li>
<li>de Vleeschauwer, H. J., THE DEVELOPMENT OF KANT'S THOUGHT (1962)</li>
<li>Findlay, J., KANT AND THE TRANSCENDENTAL OBJECT (1981)</li>
<li>Guyer, P., KANT AND THE CLAIMS OF KNOWLEDGE (1987)</li>
<li>Gram, M. S., INTERPRETING KANT (1982)</li>
<li>Gram, M. S., KANT, ONTOLOGY, AND THE A PRIORI (1968)</li>
<li>Gram, M. S., THE TRANSCENDENTAL TURN: THE FOUNDATIONS OF KANT'S IDEALISM (1984)</li>
<li>Hartnack, J., KANT'S THEORY OF KNOWLEDGE (1967)</li>
<li>Heidegger, M., KANT AND THE PROBLEM OF METAPHYSICS (1962)</li>
<li>Kitcher, P., KANT'S TRANSCENDENTAL PSYCHOLOGY (1990)</li>
<li>Martin, G., KANT'S METAPHYSICS AND THEORY OF SCIENCE (1955)</li>
<li>Melnick, A., KANT'S ANALOGIES OF EXPERIENCE (1973)</li>
<li>Melnick, A., SPACE, TIME AND THOUGHT IN KANT (1989)</li>
<li>Nagel, Gordon, THE STRUCTURE OF EXPERIENCE (1983)</li>
